ise victory at the Paris Olympics on Tuesday left spectators at an Indianapolis Catholic school cheering as a former student broke a major Olympic record and brought home a gold medal for the United States.\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 653, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 639, \"end\": 652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9975799689867811, \"rank\": 0.002425887366377001, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indianapolis native Cole Hocker astounded the sporting world on Tuesday when he clinched a last-minute win in the men's 1,500-meter race at the Paris 2024 Olympics, pulling down the gold and setting a new Olympic record of 3:27.65.\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 886, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 655, \"end\": 667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"score\": 0.9999681230298315, \"rank\": 2.446379844492911e-05, \"text\": \"Indianapolis\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBC News referred to the victory as a \\\"stunning upset\\\" as Hocker pulled past world champion Josh Kerr in the final seconds of the race, crossing the finish line with his arms outstretched.\", \"from\": 888, \"to\": 1076, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 888, \"end\": 896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_News\", \"score\": 0.9158582513849246, \"rank\": 0.07505434398357555, \"text\": \"NBC News\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_News\"}, {\"begin\": 980, \"end\": 984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"score\": 0.9003316181142381, \"rank\": 0.10476019664100904, \"text\": \"Josh\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hocker was still in third place with roughly 10 seconds left in the race before a final sprint put him just inches ahead of Kerr to take the top spot.\", \"from\": 1078, \"to\": 1228, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"WOW.\", \"from\": 1230, \"to\": 1234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1230, \"end\": 1233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WOWT\", \"score\": 0.9996434493511288, \"rank\": 0.00031958717779223534, \"text\": \"WOW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WOWT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WOWT\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\ud83d\\ude31A STUNNING upset in the men's 1500m as AMERICAN COLE HOCKER takes gold!#ParisOlympicspic.twitter.com/wlq81lbvSO  In his hometown, meanwhile, a crowd at his alma mater Cathedral High School in Indianapolis watched and cheered as Hocker pulled off the incredible win.\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1285, \"end\": 1296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"COLE HOCKER\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\"}, {\"begin\": 1429, \"end\": 1441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"score\": 0.9999681230298315, \"rank\": 2.446379844492911e-05, \"text\": \"Indianapolis\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Video shared on social media showed spectators erupting into successively louder cheers as Hocker edged ahead in the race and ultimately won it.\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1647, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Watch Party at Cathedral to watch 2019 grad, Cole Hocker win Gold \\ud83e\\udd47 !\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 